Midgaard's registry contains the founding charter of the Oathbound March, issued during the generation after the First Stone Accord.
Midgaard has issued four formal directives to rescind or modify the March's oath structure; none have been accepted by the surviving command chain.
Valid-but-not-acknowledged is Midgaard's most uncomfortable charter status: Midgaard's authority is legally intact and operationally irrelevant.
The Continuity faction argues the March's oath structure must be formally dissolved through a process the command chain accepts rather than one Midgaard unilaterally declares.
The Reckoning faction argues the command chain is not a legitimate authority and does not have standing to accept or reject dissolution processes.
This debate has been ongoing for three generations. The Oathbound dead continue patrolling. Shadowmere is an open file: a case study in what happens when emergency powers outlast the emergency and the authority that issued them.

